</a>
</article>
<article class="blog--container blog-preview">
<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2012/02/06/spring-mobile-1-0-0-rc1-released">Spring Mobile 1.0.0.RC1 Released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/55c978494c708e62f4b76bde1e0dcc19?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/rclarkson">Roy Clarkson</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-02-06 23:00:00.0">February 6, 2012</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="751" href="/blog/2012/02/06/spring-mobile-1-0-0-rc1-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Dear Spring Community,</p>
<p> We are pleased to announce that the first release candidate of the <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-mobile">Spring Mobile</a> project is now available! </p>
<p> <strong>Spring Mobile provides extensions to Spring MVC that aid in the development of cross-platform mobile web applications.</strong> The 1.0.0.RC1 release ships a general facility for user site preference management that can be used independently or in conjunction with the mobile site switcher. See the <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-mobile/docs/1.0.0.RC1/changelog.txt">changelog</a> and <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-mobile/docs/1.0.0.RC1/reference/html/">reference manual</a> for all the info. </p>
<p> <a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Mobile">Download</a> the release distribution or pull the artifacts from Maven using the following: </p>
</div>
</section>
